pageProduct.name: Scholl Party Feet Gel Cushions
pageProduct.description:
Information

Effective cushioning and protection for your feet

Partying with friends, shopping trips or sightseeing - your feet have to handle a lot when you are out and about. Don't let your feet spoil the fun. Scholl Party Feet Heel Shields give them comfort and protection. Against rubbing shoes and slipping, this insert is the right choice. You put it around the back of your heel.

Cushioning

Our GelActiv Technology helps provide effective cushioning and protection for your feet

Discreet design

Party Feet inserts are designed to be slim and discreet. They are also transparent, which makes them also invisible in the shoe.

Everywhere you go

Sightseeing, shopping trips, partying with friends or just walks in the park - Party Feet Inserts give you comfort wherever you go.

Firmly in place

Party Feet Inserts are designed with non-slip technology so the insert doesn't slip in the shoe.

General Information

Scholl Party Feet Ultra Slim Invisible Gel Cushions with adhesive technology are thinner for comfort and help reduce the burning feeling in the balls of your feet and provide excellent cushioning. Scholl Party Feet uses GelActiv Technology and has a clear gel, slim and discreet design. Party Feet ball of foot cushions fit comfortably into most women's shoes

Size: 1 Pair

Reusable?: true

KEY FEATURES

• Slimmer shape (compared to Party Feet Invisible Gel Cushions)
• Clear gel, ultra slim and discreet
• Adhesive technology
• Reusable
• Washable

Warnings

Discontinue use if discomfort or irritation occurs, do not use in contact with broken or irritated skin.

Directions

Place in your shoe under the ball of your foot.

- Identify left and right foot symbols on each cushion.
- Trial placement in the shoe before removing the protective film.
- Ensure the cushion sits under the ball of foot with the priority end facing the heel.
- Peel protective film off cushions and apply to the shoe sticky side down.
- Reposition if required, ensuring the cushions are in the same position in each shoe.
- Take care when removing, pull slowly and gently out of the shoe, applying pressure to the shoe insole next to the cushion with the other hand.
- Replace after 6 months or first signs of wear.

Recyclable Packaging?: Yes

Recycling Code: 1 PET(E)| 21 PAP

Washable?: true
